# React Native Design System Rules

These rules guide the Cursor Figma plugin (implement-design, code-connect-components) to generate production-quality React Native code.

## Component Structure

### File Organization
- One component per file at `src/components/<ComponentName>.tsx`
- Shared/reusable components at `src/components/common/`
- Screen-level components at `src/screens/`
- Component name must be PascalCase matching filename

### Component Pattern
```tsx
import React from 'react';
import { View, Text, StyleSheet, ViewStyle } from 'react-native';

interface ComponentNameProps {
  style?: ViewStyle;
  // props derived from Figma component properties
}

const ComponentName: React.FC<ComponentNameProps> = ({ style, ...props }) => {
  return (
    <View style={[styles.container, style]}>
      {/* children */}
    </View>
  );
};

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    // styles
  },
});

export default ComponentName;
```

## Styling Rules

### ALWAYS use StyleSheet.create()
- Never use inline styles except for dynamic values
- Group styles by semantic meaning, not by Figma layer name
- Use descriptive style names: `headerTitle`, `cardContainer`, not `frame1`, `rectangle2`

### Layout
- Use `flexDirection: 'column'` as default (RN default)
- Map Figma Auto Layout to flexbox: `HORIZONTAL` -> `flexDirection: 'row'`, `VERTICAL` -> `flexDirection: 'column'`
- Map Figma alignment: `MIN` -> `flex-start`, `CENTER` -> `center`, `MAX` -> `flex-end`, `SPACE_BETWEEN` -> `space-between`
- Use `gap` property for spacing between items (React Native 0.71+)
- Prefer `flex: 1` over explicit width/height for responsive layouts
- Never use absolute positioning unless the Figma design explicitly requires overlapping elements

### Dimensions
- Convert Figma px values directly to RN numbers (no units needed)
- For responsive designs, prefer percentage or flex over fixed dimensions
- Use `alignSelf: 'stretch'` for full-width containers

### Colors
- Use `rgba(r, g, b, a)` format for colors with transparency
- Use `rgb(r, g, b)` for opaque colors
- Extract repeated colors into a `colors` constant object at file top or in a shared `theme.ts`

### Typography
- Map Figma font weights: 400 -> 'normal', 700 -> 'bold', others -> string literal ('100'-'900')
- Map Figma text alignment: LEFT -> 'left', CENTER -> 'center', RIGHT -> 'right', JUSTIFIED -> 'justify'
- Include `lineHeight` when specified in Figma (use px value directly)
- Include `letterSpacing` when specified

### Shadows (Cross-Platform)
- Map Figma DROP_SHADOW to both iOS shadow properties AND Android `elevation`
- iOS: `shadowColor`, `shadowOffset`, `shadowOpacity`, `shadowRadius`
- Android: `elevation` (approximate from shadow radius)
- Use `Platform.OS` switch only when shadow rendering differs significantly

### Border Radius
- Map `cornerRadius` directly to `borderRadius`
- For individual corner radii, use `borderTopLeftRadius`, `borderTopRightRadius`, etc.

### Images
- Use `<Image source={require('./path')} />` for local assets
- Use `<Image source={{ uri: url }} />` for remote images
- Always include `resizeMode` prop
- Prefer `FastImage` from `react-native-fast-image` for remote images if available in project

## Component Mapping from Figma

| Figma Node Type | React Native Component |
|-----------------|----------------------|
| FRAME / GROUP | `<View>` |
| TEXT | `<Text>` |
| RECTANGLE (image fill) | `<Image>` |
| RECTANGLE (solid/gradient) | `<View>` |
| VECTOR / BOOLEAN_OPERATION | `<Image>` (export as PNG/SVG) |
| COMPONENT / INSTANCE | Custom component |
| ELLIPSE | `<View>` with `borderRadius: width/2` |

## What NOT to Do

- Do NOT hardcode text strings; use props or i18n keys
- Do NOT generate Figma layer IDs or internal names in output code
- Do NOT use `position: 'absolute'` for elements inside Auto Layout frames
- Do NOT use web CSS properties (`box-shadow`, `display: block`, etc.)
- Do NOT generate platform-specific code without `Platform.OS` checks
- Do NOT omit TypeScript types for props and styles
